    "summary": "I am a senior expert in payments and market infrastructures. As an electrotechnical  engineer by education, initially specialised in telecommunications, I broadened my experience into networks, complexity, economics, policy and strategy.  I have strong analytical skills, deep knowledge of various network applications, extensive international experience and adequate communication skills, particularly for policy advice to board-level. My focus is on getting things done and moved into the right direction, including through cooperation in international groups.\n\nI\u2019m passionate about learning. For me it\u2019s fun to find solutions for complicated topics, be it technical, policy or legal, especially in the more complicated international settings. I like to work with the mix of policy, economics and technology and profit in my daily work from a solid engineering background. Lately I dived into accelerating technologies and researched their increasing impact on society, the economy in particular. See the link here to my paper, that was fun to write: \nhttps://www.dnb.nl/en/binaries/OS2_tcm47-372683.pdf\n ",
